@startuml activity-inkloss-experiment
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because this is the scientific method as a control flow — hypothesis, measure,
'' observe, intervene, re-measure, confirm — with the failure state coloured red and the resolved state
'' green, from the shared palette. Mermaid cannot colour by outcome nor render byte-reproducibly.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title MathJax inline ink-loss — a reproducible experiment (hypothesis -> fix -> re-measurement)

start
:**Hypothesis.** MathJax 4 defaults `linebreaks.inline` ON;\ntypesetting off-DOM through liteAdaptor, it has no\ncontainer to measure, so it splits inline math into\none `<svg>` per break opportunity, and\n`svg:not(:root){overflow:hidden}` clips the first viewBox; <<RENDERER_FILL>>
:**Method.** Render a corpus of 154 files /\n1743 inline-math occurrences; count occurrences that\nsplit into multiple `<svg>` and those losing >50% ink; <<RENDERER_TINT>>
:**Observation.** 385 occurrences split;\n35 lost >50% of their ink;\n`\implies` / `\iff` rendered completely invisible\n(a gap of the right width, no ink, no error); <<ERROR_TINT>>
:**Intervention.** Set `linebreaks: {inline: false}`\n(each expression is rendered once, cached, injected as a\nstatic SVG into a column it cannot reflow into); <<MARKDOWN_TINT>>
:**Re-measurement.** Same corpus:\n0 occurrences split, 0 lost ink;\ndisplay math byte-identical before/after; <<MARKDOWN_FILL>>
if (split = 0 and ink-loss = 0?) then (yes)
  :**Conclusion.** Hypothesis confirmed;\nregression pinned by the electron smoke\n(fails on any CSP console message); <<MARKDOWN_TINT>>
  stop
else (no)
  :derive a new hypothesis and repeat; <<ERROR_FILL>>
  stop
endif

